{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"alias":"sediment-oscitant-snake","description":"## Why\n\nRemoving config keys leaves stale references across docs, CLI help text, and release\nnotes. This story is the accuracy sweep: delete/correct every reference to a removed\nkey and verify the config docs match the post-prune schema. It should close LAST\n(after the removal stories land) so it sweeps the final state.\n\n## What\n\nSweep and correct references to each REMOVED key:\n- `require_signature_for_close`: `docs/manifest-signing.md:60`, `docs/config.md:96,386`,\n  `docs/llm-framework.md:471`, `docs/migrations.md:142`, `docs/release-notes.md:46`,\n  `src/rebar/_cli/help/transition.txt:7`, `docs/cli-reference.md:377`.\n- `baseline_dual_write` / `baseline_consumer_swap`: `docs/jira-sync-setup.md:329-348`\n  (the phased-rollout section), `docs/config.md`, any ADR-0026 operator notes.\n- `progressive_drift_refresh` / `remediation_mode` / `novelty_drop_active`:\n  `docs/config.md`, `docs/plan-review-gate.md`, `docs/workflow-authoring-v2.md` if referenced.\n- Then a full-repo grep for each removed key name across `docs/`, `*.md`, `src/rebar/_cli/help/`.\n\nAlso: correct any doc statements that become inaccurate once behavior is hardcoded\n(e.g. \"default on; explicit false is the back-out\" must no longer imply a toggle),\nand record the KEEP decisions (signature mirror, completion floor) where docs discuss them.\n\n## Scope\n\nDocs/help/release-notes only — no behavior change. Depends on stories d6bd, 4cdf, and\nthe require_signature retirement having landed so the final state is swept.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A repo-wide grep for each removed key name (`require_signature_for_close`, `baseline_dual_write`, `baseline_consumer_swap`, `progressive_drift_refresh`, `remediation_mode`, `novelty_drop_active`) returns ZERO stale references in `docs/`, `*.md`, and CLI help.\n- [ ] Docs describing the now-hardcoded behaviors no longer describe a config toggle; the retained tuning params are still documented.\n- [ ] `docs/config.md` matches the pruned schema exactly (every listed key exists; no removed key listed).\n- [ ] CLI help (`transition` etc.) and golden help fixtures regenerated and consistent.","id":"5566-dac3-5b7f-49ae","parent_id":"8d27-7ee1-f137-4b88","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Doc-accuracy sweep: purge removed config keys, correct config docs"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783967951632805001,"uuid":"fd1476b9-30a5-4caa-96da-f121ec1042ad"}